The confessions of these nuns were accompanied by what investigators believed were classic signs of demonic possession: contortions, unnatural body movements, speaking in tongues (glossolalia), obscene insults, blasphemies, and the appearance of unexplainable wounds that vanished without aid.
After the nuns at Louviers were afflicted, authorities undertook the task of cataloguing the symptoms of demonic possession.
In the time-frame of the cases in France, demonic possession served as a catchall explanation for any personality anomaly.
